  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Characterization of posterior corneal changes in primary open angle glaucoma patients, using
      Scheimpflug examination.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A cohort of primary open angle glaucoma (POAG) patients is submitted to Scheimpflug Pentacam
      examination. The results are compared with a control group of age and central corneal
      thickness matched healthy subjects
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
